quran[182]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,By the (angels) ranged in ranks
  37,2,and the drivers driving
  37,3,and the reciters of the reminder
  37,4,"Verily, your God is one"
  37,5,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and what is between the two, and the Lord of the sunrises"
  37,6,"Verily, we have adorned the lower heaven with the adornment of the stars"
  37,7,and to preserve it from every rebellious devil
  37,8,that they may not listen to the exalted chiefs; for they are hurled at from every side
  37,9,"driven off, and for them is lasting woe"
  37,10,"save such as snatches off a word, and there follows him a darting flame"
  37,11,Ask them whether they are stronger by nature or (the angels) whom we have created? We have created them of sticky clay
  37,12,"Nay, thou dost wonder and they jest"
  37,13,and when they are reminded they will not remember
  37,14,and when they see a sign they make a jest thereof
  37,15,"and say, 'This is naught but obvious sorcery"
  37,16,"What! when we are dead, and have become earth and bones, shall we then be raised"
  37,17,what! and our fathers of yore
  37,18,"Say, 'Yes, and ye shall shrink up"
  37,19,"and it shall only be one scare, and, behold, they shall look on"
  37,20,"and they shall say, 'O, woe is us! this is the day of judgment"
  37,21,"this is the day of decision, which ye did call a lie"
  37,22,"Gather ye together, ye who were unjust, with their mates and what they used to serve"
  37,23,"beside God, and guide them to the way of hell"
  37,24,"and stop them; verily, they shall be questioned"
  37,25,Why do ye not help each other
  37,26,"nay, on that day they shall resign themselves"
  37,27,"and some shall draw near to others, to question each other"
  37,28,"and they shall say, 'Verily, ye came to us from the right"
  37,29,"They shall say, 'Nay, ye were not believers"
  37,30,"nor had we any authority over you; nay, ye were an outrageous people"
  37,31,"And the sentence of our Lord shall be due for us; verily, we shall surely taste thereof"
  37,32,"we did seduce you - verily, we were erring too"
  37,33,"therefore, verily, on that day they shall share the torment"
  37,34,thus it is that we will do with the sinners
  37,35,"Verily, when it is said to them, 'There is no god but God,' they get too big with pride"
  37,36,"and say, 'What! shall we leave our gods for an infatuated poet"
  37,37,"Nay, he came with the truth, and verified the apostles"
  37,38,"verily, ye are going to taste of grievous woe"
  37,39,nor shall ye be rewarded save for that which ye have done
  37,40,Except God's sincere servants
  37,41,these shall have a stated provision
  37,42,"of fruits, and they shall be honoured"
  37,43,in the gardens of pleasure
  37,44,upon couches facing each other
  37,45,they shall be served all round with a cup from a spring
  37,46,white and delicious to those who drink
  37,47,"wherein is no insidious spirit, nor shall they be drunk therewith"
  37,48,"and with them damsels, restraining their looks, large eyed"
  37,49,as though they were a sheltered egg
  37,50,and some shall come forward to ask others
  37,51,"and a speaker amongst them shall say, 'Verily, I had a mate"
  37,52,"who used to say, \"Art thou verily of those who credit"
  37,53,"What! when we are dead, and have become earth and bones, shall we be surely judged"
  37,54,"He will say, 'Are ye looking down"
  37,55,and he shall look down and see him in the midst of hell
  37,56,"He shall say, 'By God, thou didst nearly ruin me"
  37,57,"And had it not been for the favour of my Lord, I should have been among the arraigned"
  37,58,What! shall we not die save our first death
  37,59,and shall we not be tormented
  37,60,"Verily, this is mighty bliss"
  37,61,for the like of this then let the workers work
  37,62,"Is that better as an entertainment, or the tree of Ez Zaqqum"
  37,63,"Verily, we have made it a trial to the unjust"
  37,64,"Verily, it is a tree that comes forth from the bottom of hell"
  37,65,its spathe is as it were the heads of devils
  37,66,"verily, they shall eat therefrom, and fill their bellies therefrom"
  37,67,Then shall they have upon it a mixture of boiling water
  37,68,"then, verily, their return shall be to hell"
  37,69,"Verily, they found their fathers erring"
  37,70,and they hurried on in their tracks
  37,71,but there had erred before them most of those of yore
  37,72,and we had sent warners amongst them
  37,73,"Behold, then, what was the end of those who were warned"
  37,74,save God's sincere servants
  37,75,"Noah did call upon us, and a gracious answer did we give"
  37,76,and we saved him and his people from a mighty trouble
  37,77,and we made his seed to be the survivors
  37,78,and we left for him amongst posterity
  37,79,peace upon Noah in the worlds
  37,80,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,81,"verily, he was of our believing servants"
  37,82,Then we drowned the others
  37,83,"And, verily, of his sect was Abraham"
  37,84,when he came to his Lord with a sound heart
  37,85,"when he said to his father and his people, 'What is it that ye serve"
  37,86,with a lie do ye desire gods beside God
  37,87,What then is your thought respecting the Lord of the worlds
  37,88,And he looked a look at the stars
  37,89,"and said, 'Verily, I am sick"
  37,90,and they turned their backs upon him fleeing
  37,91,"And he went aside unto their gods and said, 'Will ye not eat"
  37,92,What ails you that ye will not speak
  37,93,And he went aside to them smiting with the right hand
  37,94,And they rushed towards him
  37,95,"Said he, 'Do ye serve what ye hew out"
  37,96,"when God has created you, and what ye make"
  37,97,"Said they, 'Build for him a pyre, and throw him into the flaming hell"
  37,98,"They desired to plot against him, but we made them inferior"
  37,99,"Said he, 'Verily, I am going to my Lord, He will guide me"
  37,100,"My Lord! grant me (a son), one of the righteous"
  37,101,and we gave him glad tidings of a clement boy
  37,102,"And when he reached the age to work with him, he said, 'O my boy! verily, I have seen in a dream that I should sacrifice thee, look then what thou seest right.' Said he, 'O my sire! do what thou art bidden; thou wilt find me, if it please God, one of the patient"
  37,103,"And when they were resigned, and Abraham had thrown him down upon his forehead"
  37,104,"we called to him, 'O Abraham"
  37,105,"thou hast verified the vision; verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,106,This is surely an obvious trial
  37,107,And we ransomed him with a mighty victim
  37,108,and we left for him amongst posterity
  37,109,Peace upon Abraham
  37,110,thus do we reward those who do well
  37,111,"verily, he was of our servants who believe"
  37,112,"And we gave him glad tidings of Isaac, a prophet among the righteous"
  37,113,"and we blessed him and Isaac;- of their seed is one who does well, and one who obviously wrongs himself"
  37,114,And we were gracious unto Moses and Aaron
  37,115,We saved them and their people from mighty trouble
  37,116,and we helped them and they had the upper hand
  37,117,and we gave them both the perspicuous Book
  37,118,and we guided them to the right way
  37,119,and we left for them amongst posterity
  37,120,Peace upon Moses and Aaron
  37,121,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,122,"verily, they were both of our servants who believe"
  37,123,And verily Elyas was of the apostles
  37,124,"when he said to his people, 'Will ye not fear"
  37,125,do ye call upon Baal and leave the best of Creators
  37,126,God your Lord and the Lord of your fathers of yore
  37,127,"But they called him liar; verily, they shall surely be arraigned"
  37,128,save God's sincere servants
  37,129,"And we, left for him amongst posterity"
  37,130,Peace upon Elyasin
  37,131,"verily, thus do we reward those who do well"
  37,132,"verily, he was of our servants who believe"
  37,133,"And, verily, Lot was surely among the apostles"
  37,134,when we saved him and his people altogether
  37,135,except an old woman amongst those who lingered
  37,136,then we destroyed the others
  37,137,"verily, ye pass by them in the morning"
  37,138,and at night; have ye then no sense
  37,139,"And, verily, Jonah was amongst the apostles"
  37,140,when he ran away into the laden ship
  37,141,and he cast lots and was of those who lost
  37,142,"and a fish swallowed him, for he was to be blamed"
  37,143,and had it not been that he was of those who celebrated God's praises
  37,144,he would surely have tarried in the belly thereof to the day when men shall be raised
  37,145,But we cast him on to the barren shore; and he was sick
  37,146,and we made to grow over him a gourd tree
  37,147,and we sent him to a hundred thousand or more
  37,148,and they believed; and we gave them enjoyment for a season
  37,149,"Ask them, 'Has thy Lord daughters while they have sons"
  37,150,or have we created the angels females while they were witnesses
  37,151,is it not of their lie that they say
  37,152,"God has begotten?' verily, they are liars"
  37,153,Has he preferred daughters to sons
  37,154,what ails you? how ye judge
  37,155,will ye not be mindful
  37,156,or have ye obvious authority
  37,157,then bring your Book if ye do speak the truth
  37,158,"And they made him to be related to the ginns, while the ginns know that they shall be arraigned"
  37,159,celebrated be God's praises from what they attribute
  37,160,save God's sincere servants
  37,161,"Verily, ye and what ye worship"
  37,162,shall not try any one concerning him
  37,163,save him who shall broil in hell
  37,164,"there is none amongst us but has his appointed place, and"
  37,165,"verily, we are ranged, and"
  37,166,"verily, we celebrate His praises"
  37,167,And yet they say
  37,168,Had we a reminder from those of yore
  37,169,we should surely have been of God's sincere servants
  37,170,But they misbelieved in it; but soon shall they know
  37,171,But our word has been passed to our servants who were sent
  37,172,that they should be helped
  37,173,"that, verily, our hosts should gain mastery for them"
  37,174,Then turn thou thy back upon them for a time
  37,175,"and look upon them, for soon they too shall look"
  37,176,Would they hasten on our torment
  37,177,"but when it descends in their court, ill will the morning be of those who have been warned"
  37,178,But turn thy back upon them for a time
  37,179,"and look, for soon they too shall look"
  37,180,"Celebrated be the praises of thy Lord, the Lord of glory, above what they attribute"
  37,181,and peace be upon the apostles
  37,182,"and praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds"